<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="44" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1303,2026]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,345,1458,1484]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">Etymology:</emphasis>
The name refers to the overlapping lateral processes of the gonopod anterior coxal folds, reminiscent of the bill in the bird genus 
<taxonomicName box="[620,687,1497,1522]" class="Diplopoda" family="Harpagophoridae" genus="Thyropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="27" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="loxia">
<emphasis box="[620,687,1497,1522]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">Loxia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(crossbills).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="27" pageNumber="44" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1303,2026]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,327,1535,1561]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">Diagnosis:</emphasis>
A species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[527,627,1536,1561]" class="Diplopoda" family="Harpagophoridae" genus="Thyropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opinatus">
<emphasis box="[527,627,1536,1561]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">opinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup. Spatulate lobe (
<emphasis box="[941,961,1536,1561]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">sl</emphasis>
) at the apical part of telopodite rounded, spoon-like. Similar in this respect to 
<taxonomicName box="[595,718,1575,1600]" class="Diplopoda" family="Harpagophoridae" genus="Thyropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="inflexus">
<emphasis box="[595,718,1575,1600]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">T. inflexus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[734,833,1575,1600]" class="Diplopoda" family="Harpagophoridae" genus="Thyropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bearti">
<emphasis box="[734,833,1575,1600]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">T. bearti</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[851,978,1575,1600]" class="Diplopoda" family="Harpagophoridae" genus="Thyropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chelatus">
<emphasis box="[851,978,1575,1600]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">T. chelatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[996,1149,1575,1600]" class="Diplopoda" family="Harpagophoridae" genus="Thyropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cristagalli">
<emphasis box="[996,1149,1575,1600]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">T. cristagalli</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1208,1428,1575,1600]" class="Diplopoda" family="Harpagophoridae" genus="Thyropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brachyacanthus">
<emphasis box="[1208,1428,1575,1600]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">T. brachyacanthus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Differs from all other species of the 
<taxonomicName box="[597,732,1613,1638]" class="Diplopoda" family="Harpagophoridae" genus="Thyropygus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Spirostreptida" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="opinatus">
<emphasis box="[597,732,1613,1638]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">T. opinatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
subgroup by having a longitudinal lateral crest (
<figureCitation box="[1327,1409,1613,1639]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,256,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[182,1401,445,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,429,1714]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Thyropygus loxia, holotype, gonopods. A: anterior view, left telopodite removed. B: posterior view, left telopodite removed. C: lateral view. D: left telopodite, anterior view. E: left telopodite, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185988/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
Fig 
<number box="[1378,1409,1613,1639]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
C, arrow) on the anterior coxal fold (
<emphasis box="[571,599,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">ac</emphasis>
); by having the tip of the lateral process of anterior coxal fold (
<emphasis box="[1387,1426,1652,1677]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">alp</emphasis>
) crossing over with opposite tip, and by having the median process of posterior coxal fold (
<emphasis box="[1210,1261,1691,1716]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">amp</emphasis>
) very small.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1303,2026]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[197,354,1728,1754]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">Description:</emphasis>
Adult male with 
<number box="[565,595,1729,1755]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" value="69.0">69</number>
podous rings, no apodous rings. Length ca. 
<quantity box="[1128,1206,1729,1755]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" unit="cm" value="10.0">10 cm</quantity>
, width ca. 
<quantity box="[1337,1432,1729,1755]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="5.5">5.5 mm</quantity>
. Adult female with 
<number box="[378,408,1768,1794]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" value="58.0">58</number>
podous rings, no apodous rings. Length ca. 
<quantity box="[942,1004,1768,1794]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="9.0" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" unit="cm" value="9.0">9 cm</quantity>
, width ca. 
<quantity box="[1136,1232,1768,1794]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.3" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" unit="mm" value="6.3">6.3 mm</quantity>
. Overall color of living animal (
<figureCitation box="[322,406,1806,1832]" captionStart="FIGURE 19. A" captionStartId="30.[151,255,1492,1516]" captionTargetBox="[162,1423,204,1458]" captionTargetId="figure@30.[151,1436,194,1468]" captionTargetPageId="30" captionText="FIGURE 19. A: Thyropygus chelatus, living male. B: Thyropygus cristagalli, living male. C: Thyropygus erectus, living male. D: Thyropygus loxia, living female." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185990/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[377,406,1806,1832]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
D) brown. Antennae and legs brownish orange.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="27.[151,1437,1303,2026]" lastBlockId="28.[151,1436,152,371]" lastPageId="28" lastPageNumber="45" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
Gonopods (
<figureCitation box="[337,434,1845,1871]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,256,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[182,1401,445,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,429,1714]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Thyropygus loxia, holotype, gonopods. A: anterior view, left telopodite removed. B: posterior view, left telopodite removed. C: lateral view. D: left telopodite, anterior view. E: left telopodite, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185988/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
Figs. 
<number box="[405,434,1845,1871]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
A–E): Anterior coxal fold (
<emphasis box="[765,793,1845,1870]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">ac</emphasis>
) (
<figureCitation box="[821,918,1845,1871]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,256,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[182,1401,445,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,429,1714]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Thyropygus loxia, holotype, gonopods. A: anterior view, left telopodite removed. B: posterior view, left telopodite removed. C: lateral view. D: left telopodite, anterior view. E: left telopodite, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185988/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
Figs. 
<number box="[889,918,1845,1871]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
A, C) with a lateral longitudinal crest (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,256,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[182,1401,445,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,429,1714]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Thyropygus loxia, holotype, gonopods. A: anterior view, left telopodite removed. B: posterior view, left telopodite removed. C: lateral view. D: left telopodite, anterior view. E: left telopodite, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185988/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,181,1884,1910]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
C, arrow); lateral process (
<emphasis box="[492,529,1884,1909]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">alp</emphasis>
) slender, regularly curved, tip crossing over with tip of opposite side, the two together forming a circle; mesal process (
<emphasis box="[655,706,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">amp</emphasis>
) very small, hump-like. Posterior coxal fold (
<emphasis box="[1264,1292,1923,1948]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">pc</emphasis>
) (
<figureCitation box="[1319,1406,1922,1948]" captionStart="FIGURE 17" captionStartId="28.[151,256,1738,1762]" captionTargetBox="[182,1401,445,1708]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[151,1436,429,1714]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURE 17. Thyropygus loxia, holotype, gonopods. A: anterior view, left telopodite removed. B: posterior view, left telopodite removed. C: lateral view. D: left telopodite, anterior view. E: left telopodite, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185988/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
Fig. 
<number box="[1376,1406,1922,1948]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" value="17.0">17</number>
</figureCitation>
B) basally with moderately high lateral paracoxites (
<emphasis box="[769,798,1961,1986]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">px</emphasis>
), distally with two processes: mesal process (
<emphasis box="[1373,1425,1961,1986]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">pmp</emphasis>
) curving caudad; lateral process (
<emphasis box="[550,589,2000,2025]" italics="true" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">plp</emphasis>
) digitiform, directed distad. Telopodite (
<figureCitation box="[1089,1188,2000,2026]" captionStart="FIGURE 16" captionStartId="26.[151,255,1847,1871]" captionTargetBox="[274,1328,454,1790]" captionTargetId="figure@26.[226,1360,436,1797]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 16. Thyropygus erectus, holotype, gonopods. A: anterior view, left telopodite removed. B: posterior view, left telopodite removed. C: left telopodite, anterior view. D: left telopodite, posterior view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/185987/files/figure.png" pageId="27" pageNumber="44">
Figs. 
<number box="[1159,1188,2000,2026]" pageId="27" pageNumber="44" value="16.0">16</number>
</figureCitation>
D–E) leaving coxite between 
<emphasis box="[259,310,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">pmp</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis box="[369,407,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">plp</emphasis>
; femoral spine (
<emphasis box="[607,628,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">fe</emphasis>
) very long, curved, 
<emphasis box="[874,949,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">in situ</emphasis>
resting curving close to 
<emphasis box="[1248,1299,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">pmp</emphasis>
; telopodite distally to 
<emphasis box="[285,308,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">fe</emphasis>
with a small round lobe (
<emphasis box="[634,658,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">lo</emphasis>
) projecting distolaterad; tibial spine (
<emphasis box="[1135,1152,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">ti</emphasis>
) very long, curving in horizontal plane under 
<emphasis box="[427,448,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">fe</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[464,538,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">in situ</emphasis>
resting close to mesal part of 
<emphasis box="[899,920,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">fe</emphasis>
; spatulate lobe (
<emphasis box="[1119,1139,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">sl</emphasis>
) basally slender, distally broadly expanded, rounded, spoon-like; palette (
<emphasis box="[738,768,268,293]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">pa</emphasis>
) simple, gutter-like, distally with about eight brownish blepharochaetae (
<emphasis box="[358,387,306,331]" italics="true" pageId="28" pageNumber="45">bp</emphasis>
).
</paragraph>
